																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>Do you want to develop your upper body muscle mass and strength at home, but don’t have any expensive equipment? Then it&#8217;s time to try calisthenics.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/training/what-is-calisthenics" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Calisthenics</a>, also known as bodyweight training, uses bodyweight resistance to promote muscle hypertrophy (muscle growth), and increase strength.</p>



<p>In this article, we discuss our calisthenics push workout. We cover the six best push exercises, technique guides, expert tips, and more.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">6 Calisthenics Push Exercises</p>



<p>These are the six best calisthenics push exercises&nbsp; for increasing muscle mass and strength in 2025:</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Push-Up">Push-up.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Pike-Push-Up">Pike Push-up.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Tricep-Extension">Tricep Extension.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Chest-Dip">Chest Dip.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Decline-Push-Up">Decline Push-up.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Diamond-Push-Up">Diamond Push-up.</a></li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Top 6 Calisthenics Push Workouts</h2>



<p>Below we have listed six of the best push calisthenics exercises for increasing muscle mass and strength. Each exercise contains a description, step-by-step guide, and expert tips. This provides you with everything you need to create a bodyweight push workout.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Push-Up">Push-Up</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">push-up</a> is a staple upper-body exercise for your calisthenics workout. The primary movers are the pectoralis major muscles. The deltoids, triceps, rectus abdominis, and obliques are the secondary movers.</p>



<p>The push-up requires the engagement of many push muscles. This makes it great for increasing upper body <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6303131/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">training volume</a> and promoting muscle growth. Furthermore, using multiple muscle groups means we can apply significant resistance, which is great for increasing mass and strength.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/957562432?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write; encrypted-media"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Push-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Kneel on your mat, lean forward, and place your palms flat on the floor shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Lift your knees off the floor to form a plank. Your weight should be resting on the balls of your feet and palms.</li>



<li>Take a deep breath in and tense your abdominal muscles.</li>



<li>Allow your elbows to bend and lower your chest toward the floor.</li>



<li>Lower until your upper arm is parallel to the floor.</li>



<li>From here, push yourself back up to the beginning position.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your hips parallel to the floor and your core engaged for the duration of the set. This will keep your torso rigid.</li>



<li>Avoid dropping during the lower phase and concentrate on lowering with control. This will help you <a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/physiology/articles/10.3389/fphys.2017.00070/full" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">develop strength</a>.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5 (Weighted)</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">12–20</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1–3 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Push-Up</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Pike-Push-Up">Pike Push-Up</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/pike-push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">pike push-up</a> is a compound movement that angles the torso to place greater emphasis on the shoulders. The primary movers are the deltoids. The secondary movers are the triceps brachii and pectoralis major.</p>



<p>The inverted position of the pike push-up mimics an overhead press, placing a greater load through the shoulders. Additionally, the <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/fulltext/2016/12000/electromyographical_comparison_of_pike_variations.20.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">core muscles</a> including the rectus abdominis, external obliques, and erector spinae must engage to stabilize our torso. This makes it a fantastic full-body exercise.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Pike Push-Ups" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980233068?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write; encrypted-media"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Pike Push-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Kneel down, lean forward, and place your palms flat on the floor.</li>



<li>Lift your knees off the floor and elevate your hips.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Your legs and torso form a 90-degree angle with the top of your head facing the floor.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your abdominal muscles.</li>



<li>Bend your elbows and lower yourself until your upper arm is horizontal.</li>



<li>Then, exhale and push yourself back up to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Perform static or dynamic hamstring stretches in your warm-up for this exercise. This will lengthen the hamstrings and make it easier to hold the pike position.</li>



<li>Beginners should perform shallow repetitions and gradually increase depth.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
